Guinea's Education Minister Siaka Barry quite agrees.

"The youth are caught up in the video games and social sites such as Facebook and won't accept a major change in the education system," he says.

"If they recognize such change, then a system comes into place. There are no clear systems now."

He notes there are plans to teach French in the native languages, replacing the FIFA-method introduced 50 years ago. This would make the education more accessible and fun for the students.

"There is progress - and there might be a few hiccups now and then."
